      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "Yes, the technology to detect stress through smart devices like voice patterns, biometric data, and usage habits is real and currently under development by major tech companies. While they may not be directly \"reading\" your emotions in real-time to control your thermostat, these systems are designed to learn your behavioral patterns so they can anticipate needs, which could theoretically be misused for surveillance or targeted advertising. This capability is a growing concern for privacy advocates who warn that it could lead to a future where your emotional state is commodified without your explicit consent.",
