      "content": "but that's exactly what makes it scary though. if they're already gathering all that data to \"improve predictive algorithms,\" then the step between predicting and actually reacting is probably tiny. if they have the data on my stress triggers, why *wouldn't* they test how an adjustment to the environment affects my behavior? it makes way more sense as a feedback loop for their AI than just some coincidence. dont u think that's a logical next step for them?",
